CatDescriptText: Penn Camera and Photo Supply Shop was located at 910 Liberty Avenue in downtown Pittsburgh by 1938.  The shop is filled with containers of chemicals, boxes of film, books and magazines, and an enlarger.  Its manager, Henry C. Cohn, may be the man blowing his nose behind the counter.  The woman beside him rests her elbow on a Speed Graphic camera box.  It is the 3 1/4 x 4 1/2 inch Anniversary model issued by Graflex between 1940 and 1947.  Harris used a Speed Graphic for most of his career, and frequently bought supplies and equipment at this shop.
TitMainTitle: Woman leaning on Graflex Speed Graphic box fixing hair, and man, possibly Henry C. Cohn, blowing nose, standing behind counter of Penn Camera and Photo Supply Shop
